## The Reference Run

A complete production run exists in the project files under `reference_run/`. When testing parsers, stage outputs, or QA logic, use these files as ground truth:

- `01_Research_Dossier.md` → 8 sections + `RESEARCH NOTES FOR STAGE 2` informal trailing section
- `02_Content_Brief.md` → contains `<!--BRIEF:` tokens AND content types table between tokens
- `03_First_Draft.md` → opens with 3-line `Target Keyword / Title Tag / Meta Description` header
- `04_Humanized_Draft.md` → article body + `## Editorial Note` (5 sub-sections)
- `05_SEO_Draft.md` → article body + `## SEO Annotation Sheet` (word count: 2776 | 2200-2800 | WITHIN TARGET)
- `06_QA_Signoff.md` → 38/39 PASS, AI Risk 5/15, Section F FLAG (client_decision type)
- `06_QA_Approved_Draft.md` → SEO draft body only; no annotation sheet
- `07_Blog_Final.html` → 784 lines; 11 CSS tokens resolved; zero internal tokens
- All handoff files → structured fields per `REFERENCE.md` handoff format

When a parser or stage produces output, compare it to the corresponding reference file.

